      "role": "user",
      "content": "the \"small actions\" thing feels like a joke tho. like, what does having a routine do when the oceans are dying and the climate is collapsing? it feels like being told to decorate the deck chairs on the Titanic. i feel like everyone is just pretending everything is fine so they dont have to face the reality that it's all over. it's exhausting to keep pretending there's a \"future\" to prepare for.",
